          <scopecontent id="aspace_9bbd5835ad6a9084a56fb3b5c0e517c8">
            <head>Scope and Contents</head>
            <p>Includes recordings of pianist Benjamin F. Ward, Jr. performing a recital for Arts in
              Duke Chapel. Selections include works by Johann Sebastian Bach; Cesar Franck; Claude
              Debussy; and Frederic Chopin. As an Adjunct Associate Professor in the Duke University
              Department of Philosophy, and the Associate Dean for Faculty Program, Ward directed
              and performed with The Pitchforks.</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
